CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18, reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley...Right center: Speaker's table in background. Seated at the table are: Mr. and Mrs. Earl Sams (she's in print dress): District Attorney Andrew T. Parks in dark suit; Mrs. Charles P. Pernell, Rev. and Mrs. Talley, Mr. and Mrs. Tinker, Norman Washington is seen on extreme left of photo. White-haired John M. Huston.  Register of Wills, is seated next to Mrs. Lella Y. Payne.  REv. J.A. Bradley is seated next to piano.  Muzette Preston, program chairman at front table, wears a corsage...Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Group of women and men including from left: three unknown, Mrs. W. D. Battles, John Cavanaugh, Martha Talley, Rev. Cornell E. Talley, Mr. and Mrs. Tinker, Mrs. Charles P. Pernell, Andrew T. Parks wearing dark suit, Mr. and Mrs. Earl Sams wearing polka dot dress, Rev. J. A. Bradley seated next to piano, Lella Y. Payne wearing sheer eyelet blouse, and John M. Huston with clasped hands, seated at long banquet table, with Norman Washington seated on left, and Muzette Preston wearing corsage in foreground, in Central Baptist Church for banquet honoring Talley
